 &HT;    Since then, Southworth has not looked back and has two more
manuscripts in search of a publisher.
 &HT;    ``I have made peace with the elements of writing, knowing that I
must write'' he said. ``So far, there has been scant monetary
return for my efforts. It came as a surprise to me that my greatest
satisfaction has been the acceptance, the little bit of praise for
my efforts. The author wants and needs to be read, despite the
nonsense that the author writes only for himself. If that were
true, why would he write down his thoughts at all, or, having
written them down, why show them to anyone else?''
 &HT;    The Southworths get out of bed each morning at 7:30. While
Violet prepares a light breakfast and tends her magnificent
collection of African violets, her husband heads straight to the
