<SLUG> BC-CRUISE-CALL-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PHOTOGRAPHER SUSPECTED OF TAPPING TOM CRUISE'S PHONE   CALL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Will also move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.) 
BY PETER HARTLAUB  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Federal authorities have arrested an L.A.-area
photographer, claiming he used a scanner to tap a movie-set cell
phone call between actors Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman, then sold
the conversation to the tabloids.
</P>
<P>
   Eric Ford, 27, arrested Thursday, faces three counts of
wiretapping and could serve 15 years in prison if convicted. The
charges are related to the alleged interception of the cellular
phone call and the selling of the conversation, which appeared in
the June 30 issue of the Globe.
</P>
<P>
   A grand jury unsealed an indictment against Ford early this
week, and he was arrested about 6 a.m. Thursday by FBI agents at
his home in Studio City, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Assistant U.S. Attorney Gregory Jessner said the alleged
interception occurred in February on a Studio City movie set. The
U.S. Attorney's Office was contacted by Cruise's attorney after the
tabloid article was published.
</P>
<P>
   ``My understanding is that Mrs. Kidman was using a cellular
phone somewhere on the set of `Practical Magic,' and Mr. Cruise was
at home,'' Jessner said, adding that officials believe Ford was
following the actress.
</P>
<P>
   Ford was ushered into his bail hearing by federal marshals
Thursday afternoon and was released after his girlfriend pledged to
put up $10,000 for his release.
</P>
<P>
   Ford is scheduled to return to court Monday to enter a plea.
</P>
<P>
   The Globe story, headlined ``Is Tom Cruise's Marriage Hanging By
A Thread?'' does not mention Ford by name but quotes an anonymous
source. The article describes an angry conversation between Cruise
and Kidman but does not provide a transcript of the tape and even
suggests that it might be a fake.
</P>
<P>
   The Globe released a short statement, contending that it ``did
nothing illegal or improper in putting together this story.''
</P>
<P>
   Cruise and Kidman, through their publicist, declined to comment.
</P>
<P>
   The couple met on the set of ``Days of Thunder,'' were later
married and acted together again in ``Far and Away.'' Their third
film together, Stanley Kubrick's ``Eyes Wide Shut,'' has been
shrouded in secrecy and is scheduled for release next year.
</P>
<P>
   Jessner, who called Ford a ``paparazzi,'' said the U.S.
Attorney's Office did not go after the cameraman because of the
celebrities' involvement.
</P>
<P>
   ``This crime is a crime we take very seriously,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Studio City is a Los Angeles suburb. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
