<HEADLINE>
YOUNG LOSES OUT ON HAWAII JOB
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC defensive coordinator Bill Young lost out to
San Diego Chargers interim coach June Jones for the head-coaching
position at the University of Hawaii.
</P>
<P>
   Jones was named Hawaii's coach on Thursday afternoon, two days
after Hawaii interviewed him and Young in Southern California.
Hawaii officials told Young he was their second choice for the job.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's flattering to even be considered,'' Young said. ``I've
got a great place to be right here. It may be a blessing.''
</P>
<P>
   Other candidates for the job included Arizona assistant coach
Duane Akina and Utah coach Ron McBride, who withdrew himself from
consideration Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Football awards: Linebacker Chris Claiborne was named most
valuable player at USC's football awards banquet Thursday night at
the Biltmore Hotel.
</P>
<P>
   Senior defensive tackle Marc Matock was named most inspirational
player, after returning from a midseason broken ankle.
</P>
<P>
   Other winners were offensive guard Travis Claridge and defensive
tackle Ennis Davis for linemen of the year; free safety Ifeanyi
Ohalete for special teams player of the year; offensive guard Zach
Wilson and linebacker Rocky Seto for top scout team players; free
safety Rashard Cook for player of the game against Notre Dame;
tailback Frank Strong for longest run of the season; kicker Adam
Abrams for academic achievement and defensive tackle Aaron Williams
for underclassman with outstanding athletic ability, academics and
character.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
