<P>
   TV-TEMPEST (Undated) _ Though hardly a disaster, NBC's
``Tempest'' Sunday night is a morality play that works well for an
hour or so, and then begins to crumble in an allegorical war story
that is more confusing than enlightening. NBC is resting its hopes
here on Peter Fonda, who brings to ``The Tempest'' the quiet
intensity that got him an Oscar nomination for his portrayal of a
stoic Southern beekeeper in ``Ulee's Gold.''
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
