The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
MENORAHS-HOLIDAY (Los Angeles) _ Menorahs are central to
celebration of the Jewish holiday of Hanukkah. But it doesn't have
to be a simple candelabra. These Hanukkah lamps come in every
material, in every color and size. We show the variety of designs,
and tell the story behind Hanukkah that makes the lighting of the
candles for eight nights special. By Carol Bidwell. 
. 
HOT-TIPS (Los Angeles) _ Ever notice how the December issues of
fashion mags are always filled with the faces of time? Some
watchmakers feature their wares next to the face of supermodels
like Cindy Crawford, others let the wristwatches stand alone as
works of art. Regardless, a watch fits all sizes. And can be easily
exchanged. By Barbara De Witt. 

