<TEXT>
<P>
   Entertainment and culture stories from The N.Y. Times News
Service for Saturday, Dec. 12.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Ideas Page &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MUSICALS-TABOO (New York) _ What is and is not appropriate as a
subject for a musical play. Moving with a short introduction and
three essays:
</P>
<P>
   MUSICALS-KRIEGER (New York) _ By Henry Krieger, whose play
``Side Show,'' met with resistance. (800 words)
</P>
<P>
   MUSICALS-COMDEN (New York) _ By Betty Comden and Adolph Green,
who over the decades have seen all matter of subjects made to sing
and dance on Broadway, including their shows ``On the Town'' and
``Peter Pan.'' (750 words)
</P>
<P>
   MUSICALS-BISHOP (New York) _ By Andre Bishop, the artistic
director of Lincoln Center and a producer of ``Parade.'' (700
words)
</P>
<P>
   FREUD-GAYS (Undated) _ Psychoanalysts, the diehards among
therapists in the argument that homosexuality is a mental
disturbance, have turned themselves around, and are going so far as
to argue this month that it is homophobia that is a sign of
disturbance. By Erica Goode. (1600 words)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL-BIOGRAPHY (Undated) _ After 10 years of work, Oxford
will publish the 24-volume American National Biography next month.
With 17,450 biographies, the publishers hope to create a
comprehensive portrait of American history. How to navigate such a
massive collection? You could try looking up entries under subject
matter, contributor or place of birth. But the most interesting
index by far is the one organized by ``Occupation and Realms of
Renown.'' There you can find even the uncommon protagonists _
Chanters, Blind People, Christian Converts, Fluegelhorn Players,
Smugglers, Gurus, Gangsters, Undertakers and Murder Victims (Crazy
Horse makes this list). By Joyce Jensen. (1000 words)
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867 or (212) 556-1927. And be sure to look for other
entertainment stories from our partners: Bloomberg News, The Boston
Globe, Cox News Service, Hearst Newspapers, The Houston Chronicle,
The Arizona Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram,
Los Angeles Daily News, San Francisco Chronicle and Seattle
Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
