</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Texas export growth for the first nine months of this
year slowed to one-third of its 1997 rate as the Asian economic
crisis sapped its double-digit power of recent years. Total exports
are up 5.1 percent for the first nine months of 1998, to $64.71
billion, a $3.12 billion increase. That compares with a growth rate
of 13.9 percent for all of 1997 and reflects weaknesses in the
Asian and South American markets, according to the Texas Department
of Economic Development. By BILL BOWEN. Story has moved in ``f''
financial category. &QL; 
