<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The little houses and figurines that began
as coffee-table decorations, set in nests of cotton and glitter,
have taken over entire rooms in many collectors' homes. Some of the
more elaborate collections now have not only their own boats, but
also their own trucks, trains and motorcycles, ice palaces,
Italian-style carved marble fountains that spout real water and
McDonald's hamburger joints. This rampant building has snowballed
Christmas collectibles into a billion-dollar-a-year business. By
CAROLYN POIROT. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
