<P>
   STAPLES-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ A childlike faith should permeate the whole Christmas
season, not because of Santa, but because of Christ's birth and
what that means. You see, I love the blessing and mystery that are
Christmas. I like that it represents the fulfillment of prophecy,
the birth of the Messiah. And what could be more mysterious than a
virgin giving birth? What could be a more perfect gift to us all?
What, indeed, requires more faith? By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES. Story
has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
