<P>
   BENGALS _ Since 1991, the Cincinnati Bengals have been the
losingest team in the National Football League. The Bengals, a
family operation, have a skeleton scouting staff that has blown one
high draft pick after another. Fans support has begun to waver and
season-ticket holders are now calling for team owner Mike Brown to
resign as general manager. We explore the issues behind the
league's worst team of this decade. (Williams/Chick
Ludwig/McClelland, Dayton Daily News). 50.
</P>
