   &UR; FOLD: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-MOOD (Washington) _ This is how it was to be Bill
Clinton this week: Holding a round of cheery Christmas parties
where your guests gobble your baby lamb chops and speculate, out of
your earshot, whether you will keep your job. Attending a private
viewing of ``Enemy of the State,'' even as you are accused of being
just that. By James Bennet and Melinda Henneberger.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `w' category.)
</P>
<P>
   2-column hed.
</P>
<P>
   3-column photo with IMPEACH; story on TOP.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-CLINTON (Washington) _ President Clinton speaks to the
people before committee takes vote on first of four articles. By
John M. Broder.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `w' category.)
</P>
<P>
   3-column hed.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-ASSESS (Washington) _ Why, when the people have made
limpidly clear their view that Clinton should not be impeached _
polls, election _ do the Republicans press on. A news analysis by
R.W. Apple Jr.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `w' category.) &QL;
