   &UR; INSIDE STORIES PROMOTED ON PAGE 1: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FREUD-GAYS (Undated) _ Nothing happens quickly in
psychoanalysis, and the shift in attitudes about homosexuality is
no exception. Unlike the American Psychiatric Association, which
removed homosexuality from its list of mental disorders in 1973,
psychoanalysts persisted well into the 1980s in describing
homosexuality as a ``perversion,'' and analysts continued to speak
of their ability to ``cure'' the ``serious character disorders'' of
their gay patients. By Erica Goode.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `e' category.)
</P>
<P>
   PINOCHET (London) _ Making his first appearance in public since
his arrest two months ago, Gen. Augusto Pinochet, the former
Chilean dictator, sternly told a London court Friday that he did
not acknowledge the right of any court outside his own country to
consider charges against him. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `i' category.)
</P>
<P>
   RETAIL-OUTLOOK (Undated) _ Warm weather melts winter buying
habits and sales forecasts. By Sharon R. King.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `f' category.)
</P>
<P>
   PUERTO-POLITICS (San Juan, P.R.) _ The House this year passed a
bill that would have allowed a federally sponsored referendum on
Puerto Rico's status this year, which marks the 100th anniversary
of the takeover of Puerto Rico by the United States from Spain
after the Spanish-American War. But the proposal stalled in the
Senate. Puerto Ricans remain at odds over whether to cement their
ties with the United States with statehood or seek more autonomy,
but most are united in holding on to three elements of their
identity _ Spanish language, Latin American culture and American
citizenship. By Mireya Navarro.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move this story by 9 p.m. ET in `a' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-U.S. (Washington) _ While Israel has frozen its
compliance with the Wye accords, the Palestinian Authority is not
fully complying with its own commitments at Wye, senior American
and Israeli officials said Friday. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move this story by 9 p.m. ET in `i' news file.)
</P>
