   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-APOLOGY (Washington) _ President Clinton delivers a new
statement of contrition in a last-ditch bid to stave off an
impeachment vote in the House. We look at Clinton's record of such
statements. By STEWART M. POWELL. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-IMPEACH (Washington) _ The House Judiciary Committee
debates the four articles of impeachment against President Clinton
over his handling of the Monica Lewinsky affair. By JOHN C. HENRY.
</P>
<P>
   JACKSON-LEE-IMPEACH (Washington) _ A look at the central role of
Rep. Sheila Jackson Lee, D-Texas, in the president's defense
effort. We consider her role in developing a censure resolution as
a counterweight to the articles of impeachment drafted by the
majority Republicans on the committee. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   BARR-IMPEACH (Washington) _ With the House Judiciary Committee's
approval of impeachment articles against the president, Republican
committee member Bob Barr passed another milestone in his long
battle to remove Bill Clinton from office. His fight began well
before the name Monica Lewinsky became a household name. By MARK
HELM. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-MIDEAST (Washington) _ In a trip fraught with political
peril, President Clinton travels Saturday to Israel and
Palestinian-controlled territories as he attempts to revive a
faltering 2-month-old peace plan. By NANCY MATHIS. (Already filed.)
</P>
