   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-TEXAS (Austin, Texas) _ A national arbitration panel
awards the lawyers involved in the Texas tobacco settlement $3.3
billion. The decision means the state will not have to pay any
money to the five lawyers for their work in the landmark tobacco
case, people familiar with the proceedings say. By CLAY ROBISON.
(Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-ESCAPE-JUVENILES (Bryan, Texas) _ Just two weeks after a
convicted murderer escaped from death row, 11 teen-age inmates,
including three violent offenders, escaped from the state's largest
youth correctional facility. Five were recaptured not long after
the escape. By ALLAN TURNER and PATTY REINERT. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GLF-NBA-TALKS (Undated) _ Top NBA negotiators have been meeting
secretly in an effort to end the lockout that is threatening the
entire NBA season, and there is hope that some progress is finally
being made. By MICHAEL MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-HEISMAN (New York) _ He has already won the Doak Walker
Award as the nation's top running back. And the Player of the Year
Award. And the Maxwell Award. Now, University of Texas running back
Ricky Williams is the overwhelming favorite to win the Heisman
Trophy on Saturday. By JEROME SOLOMON.
</P>
<P>
   With: FBC-LOPEZ-COLUMN.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-CLEMENS (Nashville, Tenn.) _ As the baseball winter meetings
open in Nashville, the chase for pitcher Roger Clemens continues to
dominate the discussion. An update on where the trade talks stand.
By CARLTON THOMPSON and JOSEPH DUARTE.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PRESIDENTS CUP (Melbourne, Australia) _ Complete coverage of
the second day of the Presidents Cup golf event, in which in the
International team holds a 7-3 edge over the Americans after the
opening day. By EDDIE SEFKO.
</P>
