<HEADLINE>
BAFFERT DUO HEADS FUTURITY PACK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ Premier Property and jockey David Flores are
solid, 7-5 favorites to win for the fourth time in as many races
together in the $450,000 Hollywood Futurity for 2-year-olds today
at Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Premier Property and 2-1 second choice Prime Timber are trained
by Bob Baffert, whose Real Quiet won the 1 1/16-mile Futurity in
1997 on his way to winning the Kentucky Derby and the Preakness
Stakes.
</P>
<P>
   The six-horse field includes Buck Trout, whose trainer Mike
Harrington won the Futurity with Swiss Yodeler in 1996, and
Tactical Cat, whose trainer D. Wayne Lukas won the race with
Stalwart in 1981 and Grand Canyon in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   Also on the 12:30 p.m. card today is the $500,000 Hollywood Turf
Cup, in which the Allen Paulson-owned entry of Yagli and Rice are
joint favorites, and the $100,000 Vernon O. Underwood Stakes, in
which Love That Jazz will try to join Lovelier Linda (1984) and
Meafara (1993) as the only fillies to win the 17-year-old race.
</P>
</TEXT>
