perfection in seven minutes flat. For that skill, her clients are
willing to overlook a manner that can be as sharp as her flashing
metal tweezers. (Barbara Alper/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) WASHINGTON-- Dec. 11, 1998 -- IMPEACH-MOOD, 12-11 --
President Clinton shows Nicaraguan President Arnoldo Aleman where
to stand during an event at the White House on Friday announcing
additional U.S. assistance to Central American countries devastated
by Hurricane Mitch. Fourth from right is Salvadoran President
Armando Calderon Sol. Honduran President Carlos Roberto Flores is
third from right. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
