pronounced ESS-kuh-lade and defined by Webster's as ``the act of
scaling or climbing the walls of a fortified place using ladders''
- is the first truck to be produced by Cadillac in its 96 years of
existence. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) UNDATED -- Dec. 11, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., DEC. 13 --
ABOUT-CARS-ESCALADE-1, 12-11 -- The Escalade - pronounced
ESS-kuh-lade and defined by Webster's as ``the act of scaling or
climbing the walls of a fortified place using ladders'' - is the
first truck to be produced by Cadillac in its 96 years of
existence. The Escalade's capabilities, like those of most
luxo-barge four-by-fours, will rarely be used to their potential.
(New York Times Photo)
</P>
