benefit the most from the introduction of the euro is like picking
the best-looking from a bowl of cherries. ``The bottoms-up story in
Europe is the changing shape of businesses and balance sheets, and
the recognition that shareholders are important,'' he says.
(Jonathan Player/New York Times Photo)
</P>
