   (NYT5) PARIS -- Dec. 11, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., DEC. 13 --
BIZ-FRENCH-OIL-2, 12-11 -- Though Thierry Desmarest, chairman of
Total, says its acquisition of Petrofina will bolster profits, some
analysts have criticized the deal, saying it will add more
``downstream'' oil operations, like gas stations, to Total's mix.
``Over the next five years, our concern was to have our downstream
pole strong enough,'' says Desmarest in his defense. (Owen
Franken/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) PARIS -- Dec. 11, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., DEC. 13 --
BIZ-FRENCH-OIL-1, 12-11 -- Thierry Desmarest, chairman of Total,
